<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 2:39PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Pulaski, northwestern Floyd, east central Wythe,
northeastern Carroll and southwestern Montgomery Counties and the
City of Radford through 315 PM EDT...
At 238 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Allisonia, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Christiansburg...
Radford...
Dublin...
Floyd...
Indian Valley...
Pilot...
and Patterson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
